#HTML pages Structure : 
 

<!DOCTYPE html> <!-- informing the browser that this is a HTML5 document -->

<html lang="en"> <!-- Defines the root element, specifying the language -->

<head> <!--   Contain the meta-data about the document -->
     <title>First Code</title> <!-- Sets the title of the document -->
</head>
<body> <!-- Contains the visible content of the document -->
        <h1>Heading 1</h1> <!-- Defines the main heading of the page -->
        <a href="https://google.com">Home</a> <!-- Represents a list item with a hyperlink -->
  
</body>
</html> <!-- Closing the root element-->






#HTML headings : 



HTML headings are titles or subtitles that you want to display on a web

<h1> defines the most important heading.</h1>
<h6> defines the least important heading.</h6>

It is important to use headings to show the document structure.

<h1> headings should be used for main headings, followed by <h2>

Each HTML heading has a default size.  you can specify the size for any heading using  CSS








#images :

<img src="image.jpg" alt="Description of the image">
<img>: This is the image tag.

src: This attribute specifies the URL of the image.
alt: This attribute provides alternative text for an image.






#Paragraphs and Typography : 

<p>This is a paragraph.</p>   <!-- The HTML <p> element defines a paragraph. -->

<p>This is<br>a paragraph<br>with line breaks.</p>   <!-- The HTML <br> element defines a line break. -->

<p>Lorem ipsum <small>DOLORE</small> sit, <b></b> consectetur <mark>adipisicing</mark> elit. Unde <strong>quidem</strong>, quo mollitia , <i>odit</ii> minus <sub>omnis</sub> <sup>ipsa</sup> nam <del>accusantium</del> cum dolore quibusdam? Sapiente optio odit eveniet minus sint animi laudantium nam?<ins>this is new text</p>


#Links :

HTML links are hyperlinks.

clicking on the link allow you to navigate between the documents . 


<a href="url">link text</a>

<a href="https://google.com">Google</a>




