#difference between inline and block elements : 


<!-- Block-Level Elements -->
<h1  >Block Level Elements</h1>
<h3>Hello! I'm a heading tag and I take every space available</h3>
<p>Hello! I'm a paragrapgh tag, and I take every space available</p>
<div>I'm also a block element</div> <div>I'm also a block element</div>



<!-- Inline-Level Elements -->

<h1>Inline Level Elements</h1>

<p>image tag is a good example of an inline element:</p>

<img width="150px" height="150px" src="https://dcist.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/04/Gem2-1500x1346.jpg" alt="Cat">
<img width="150px" height="150px" src="https://dcist.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/04/Gem2-1500x1346.jpg" alt="Cat">

<p>Also, the anchor tag is a good example of an inline element:</p>

<a href="https://www.facebook.com/">Go to Facebook</a>
<a href="https://www.instagram.com/?hl=en">Go to Instagram</a>